reviews.review: The Rise of Skywalker is the perfect end to the Skywalker Saga. It’s fun and entertains and does SOOOO MUCH to fix everything The Last Jedi messed up. The characters are actually likeable and the story just makes sense. I can’t give it a 5/5 because the pacing is a little bit rushed, but it needed to be because JJ Abrams had a lot to cram in in order to remedy everything Rian Johnson messes up.

Really enjoyed this one. It was excellent for what it was. A lot of cool Star Wars lore unfolding on the big screen bigger and bolder than anything you've ever seen. I can accept all the reveals and be ok with it as a fan. The whole sequel trilogy relies too heavily on the originals and I consider the originals to be the best. This movie had a virtually impossible task to wrap up and tie all 9 films. It doesn't really wrap up the prequels the way I had hoped. I honestly do not think having the sequels continue a conflict with the empire made any sense or was a good idea. The film also tries to do too much. Despite all that, this is a good Star Wars film. I love Star Wars. I can be as critical as any fan out there but at the end of the day I will watch any Star Wars film in theaters. It is a special treat.I really liked this one.
Long live JJ Abrams! Phenomenal movie!

I enjoyed the visuals, and the Characters. Could have used a little more back stories on a few things that were brought up. However, it was the best of the last three trilogy's. As someone who has read over 30 Star wars books, there was a way better trilogy already out there. But as far as the Disney version goes. This one was better than the last two. I'm a Star wars fan, and even with all its flaws, it's still a Star wars story and I take it as such. Too much negativity out there, not going to get it here.
perfect ending to what has been with me for decades
Good action like the previous JJ flick, but the film is a hollow shell. The spirit of the real Star Wars is dead. You need a plan before you take on a trilogy project of this magnitude.
it was crap, hoenstly it was worse than the second of this new trilogy, and frankly it makes the prequals look like gems in comparison.
They ended it everything in a good way. Sure there could be a little thing here or there. They keep you guessing the whole way. Perfect mix of humor and tension. Not disappointed at all.
So, this is it. Ending of Star Wars Saga, Pretty cool, but i missed something. What? I cant say.

To be honest, this film uses elements of Episosed 4,5,6 in it.  It really feels like you are watching multiple movies not a single movie.  How Palpatine survived is never explained.  How the interaction between Rey and Kylo when they are physically in 2 different places (along with how someone could teleport a light saber between people).  Elements in this film contradict the Episode....Luke's force ghost catches Rey's light saber as she is throwing it in the fire, telling her that a light saber deserves better respect, yet he threw away his light saber when Rey first gave it to him.  I could go on and on about contradictions but all you need to know is the majority of the spoilers posted prior to the movie came out are true!  Save your money and wait until this comes out on cable!
